Chirag Jain
Patrick Flick
Tony Pan

Introduction
============

Parallel metagenomic assembler designed to handle very large datasets. Program identifies the disconnected subgraphs in the de Bruijn graph, partitions the input dataset and runs a known assember independently on the partitions.

Install
=======

The repository and external submodules can be cloned directly:
git clone --recursive <GITHUB_URL>
mkdir build_directory
cd build_directory
cmake ../Metag_partitioning
make 

Run
===

Inside the build directory, 
mpirun -np <COUNT OF PROCESSES> ./bin/getHistogram <FASTQ_FILE>

Dependency
=========

External git submodules:
BLISS
mxx
velvet



